title: Volleyball Roundup: Ridgewood advances
text:

Ridgewood 3, Newcomerstown 0 
Host Ridgewood defeated Newcomerstown 25-12, 25-10, 25-10 Tuesday in Division III district tournament play. The third-seeded Generals (20-3) will host a district quarterfinal match at 4 p.m. Saturday against the winner of Tuesday nightâ€™s match between sixth-seeded Martins Ferry and eighth-seeded Edison. 
Laura Crawford had 15 kills, 11 digs, three blocks and four aces for the Generals; Eliza Haynes had 17 assists, three blocks, four digs, two kills and three aces; Allie Dobson had six kills and eight blocks; Morgan McDorman had 10 digs; Sydney Zinkon had 12 assists, six digs and three aces; Autumn Brown had four kills and one block; Cassie Mladek had three kills and three blocks; and Erinn Buchanan had two kills and three blocks. 
Sandy Valley 3, Coshocton 1 
Coshocton (8-15) lost 25-22, 17-25, 21-25, 21-25 Tuesday at seventh-seeded Sandy Valley in the opening round of Division III district volleyball. Lauren Hire had 13 kills, 20 digs and 13 assists for the 11th-seeded Redskins; Courtney Guthrie had 29 digs; Bri Newell had nine points and four aces; and Kennedy Haley had eight kills and 14 blocks.
